# Modelfile for qwen2.5vl-caption
#
# Registers a trimmed variant of qwen2.5vl:7b for use by OllamaCaptioningEngine.
#
# Why num_ctx 2048?
# -----------------
# qwen2.5vl:7b's default context window is 128,000 tokens. Ollama allocates KV
# cache proportional to num_ctx at model load time — 128k costs ~2GB of extra
# RAM and dominates inference even when actual token usage is tiny.
#
# OllamaCaptioningEngine resizes every image to 512px before encoding (same
# ceiling as the CLIP pipeline). Measured token budget at 512px:
#
#   Vision tokens  ~200–250  (measured: 247 on a 12MB full-res camera JPEG)
#   Prompt text    ~270      (the captioning paragraph prompt)
#   Response cap    500      (num_predict in OllamaCaptioningEngine)
#   ─────────────────────────
#   Measured total ~1,020
#
# 2048 gives ~2.5× headroom above measured usage. For reference: sending the
# same image at full resolution used 2,677 prompt tokens, exceeding this budget
# entirely and causing degenerate output.
#
# Do not raise this casually — even 4096 doubles the KV cache cost for no
# benefit at these input sizes. If you change num_predict or the prompt
# substantially, re-measure with: ollama run qwen2.5vl:7b + check prompt_eval_count.

FROM qwen2.5vl:7b
PARAMETER num_ctx 2048
